 
The 'iitem' package:
--------------------

This package offers the new commands \iitem, \iiitem and \ivtem.

Instead of writing long lists:
\begin{enumerate}%
\item 1
\begin{enumerate}%
\item 2
\begin{enumerate}%
\item 3
\begin{enumerate}%
\item 4
\end{enumerate}
\end{enumerate}
\item 2.1
\end{enumerate}
\end{enumerate}

you can just write
\begin{enumerate}%
\item 1
\iitem 2
\iiitem 3
\ivtem 4
\iitem 2.1
\end{enumerate}

It also works with itemize, description, compactitem, etc.

But they don't work in footnotes, marginpars ("fragile") commands.

